            "text": "/v1/health",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for status checks. Authentication is handled via API keys, and requests must include headers for content type and authorization. Response formats are JSON-based, with fields for predictions, confidence scores, and metadata. Ensure your client handles HTTP status codes like 200 for success, 429 for rate limits, and 500 for server errors."
          }
